** To be successful you will: **   
• Be a collaborative team player with a track record of working closely with
crossfunctional teams, with a focus on building relationships to promote
continuous improvement across the department.  
• Strong stakeholder management experience across a broad range of
stakeholders.  
• Demonstrated highly developed communication skills, interpersonal, written,
presentation and consultation skills, with an ability to clearly articulate
messages to a variety of audiences.  
• Demonstrated knowledge and application of Queensland Government ICT
standards, guidelines, frameworks, and governance processes to support advice
and communication to business partners and stakeholders.  
• Contribute to strategic ICT planning, development of digital governance, ICT
policies and strategies to advance the department's and Queensland
Government's digital priorities.  
• Develop and facilitate corporate training and awareness activities to
support compliance with legislative, governance, information management,
security, and digital processes.  
• Demonstrated experience across ICT or digital roles, bringing your knowledge
and expertise to support strategic governance across the department.

** What we offer: **   
\- Flexible workplace arrangements  
\- Beautifully designed offices at 140 Creek Street, Brisbane CBD  
\- A rewarding role with professional development opportunities  
\- A highly supportive culture that values diversity and inclusion while
contributing to team success.  
\- Access to and use of well-equipped end-of-trip facilities.

Applications will remain current for 12 months.

